definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  beta-D-glucose 1-phosphate -eq- beta-D-glucose 6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  betaine aldehyde + NAD+ + H2O -eq- betaine + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  P(1),P(4)-bis(5'-adenosyl) tetraphosphate + H(2)O -eq- 2 ADP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + NH3 + CO2 -eq- ADP + carbamoyl phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  CO + H2O + ferrocytochrome b-561 -eq- CO2 + 2 H+ + 2 ferricytochrome b-561.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-carboxymethylenebut-2-en-4-olide + H2O -eq- 4 oxohex-2-enedioate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-carboxyvinyl carboxyphosphonate -eq- 3-(hydrohydroxyphosphoryl)pyruvate + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phosphatidylglycerol + phosphatidylglycerol -eq- diphosphatidylglycerol (cardiolipin) + glycerol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-carnitine -eq- L-carnitine.
Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-beta-D-glucosidic linkages in cellulose, lichenin and cereal beta-D-glucans.
Catalysis of the reaction -  chloramphenicol + acetyl-CoA -eq- chloramphenicol 3-acetate + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  A + choline -eq- AH(2) + betaine aldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  chorismate -eq- 4-hydroxybenzoate + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + citrate -eq- acetate + (3S)-citryl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  citrate -eq- acetate + oxaloacetate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (3S)-citryl-CoA -eq- acetyl-CoA + oxaloacetate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + cob(I)alamin + H2O -eq- phosphate + diphosphate + adenosylcobalamin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  adenosylcobinamide-GDP + alpha-ribazole-5'-phosphate -eq- adenosylcobalamin-5'-phosphate + GMP.

Catalysis of the reaction -  cobinamide + ATP -eq- cobinamide phosphate + ADP. This reaction is the phosphorylation of the hydroxyl group of the 1-amino-2-propanol residue of cobinamide, in the presence of ATP, to form cobinamide phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  adenosylcobinamide phosphate + GTP + 2 H(+) -eq- adenosylcobinamide-GDP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage at a junction such as a reciprocal single-stranded crossover between two homologous DNA duplexes (Holliday junction).
Catalysis of the reaction -  Cu+ + NAD+ + H+ -eq- Cu2+ + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cyanate + H2O -eq- carbamate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + phospholipid olefinic fatty acid -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + phospholipid cyclopropane fatty acid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-sulfinoalanine -eq- L-alanine + sulfite.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ubiquinol + O2 -eq- ubiquinone + 2 H2O -  cytochrome O is the electron acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  deoxy-ATP + H2O -eq- dAMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dCTP + H2O -eq- dUTP + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dTDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-alpha-D-glucose -eq- dTDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-L-mannose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dTDP-6-deoxy-L-mannose + NADP(+) -eq- dTDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-L-mannose + H(+) + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dGTP + H(2)O -eq- 2'-deoxyguanosine + 2 H(+) + triphosphate.
Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage to 5'-phosphooligonucleotide end-products.
Catalysis of the reaction -  di-trans-poly-cis-decaprenyl diphosphate + isopentenyl diphosphate -eq- diphosphate + di-trans-poly-cis-undecaprenyl diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,5-diamino-6-hydroxy-4-(5-phosphoribosylamino)-pyrimidine + H(2)O + H(+) -eq- 5-amino-6-(5-phosphoribosylamino)uracil + NH(4)(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  meso-2,6-diaminopimelate + H(+) -eq- L-lysine + CO(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  LL-2,6-diaminopimelate -eq- meso-2,6-diaminopimelate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,3-diaminopropionate + H2O -eq- pyruvate + 2 NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-2,3,4,5-tetrahydropyridine-2,6-dicarboxylate + NAD(P)+ + H2O -eq- (2S,4S)-4-hydroxy-2,3,4,5-tetrahydrodipicolinate + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  pyruvate + L-aspartate-4-semialdehyde -eq- (2S,4S)-4-hydroxy-2,3,4,5-tetrahydrodipicolinate + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + dihydropterate + L-glutamate -eq- ADP + phosphate + dihydrofolate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  diphosphate + a purine nucleoside -eq- monophosphate + a purine mononucleotide.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of nonterminal (1--gt-4)-beta linkages of N-acetyl-D-glucosamine (GlcNAc) polymers of chitin and chitodextrins. Typically, endochitinases cleave randomly within the chitin chain.
Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage to 3'-phosphomononucleotides and 3'-phosphooligonucleotides with 2',3'-cyclic phosphate intermediates.
Catalysis of the reaction -  enterobactin + 3 H2O -eq- 3 N-23-dihydroxybenzoyl-L-serine + 3 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ethanolamine -eq- acetaldehyde + NH3.
Catalysis of the degradation of single-stranded DNA. It acts progressively in a 3' to 5' direction, releasing 5'-phosphomononucleotides.
Catalysis of the degradation of double-stranded DNA. It acts progressively in a 3' to 5' direction, releasing 5'-phosphomononucleotides.
Catalysis of the exonucleolytic cleavage (in the presence of ATP) in either 5' to 3' or 3' to 5' direction to yield 5'-phosphooligonucleotides.
Catalysis of the exonucleolytic cleavage in either 5' to 3' or 3' to 5' direction to yield 5'-phosphomononucleotides.
Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage of supercoiled plasma DNA to linear DNA duplexes.
